body:
I found a stable solution, but it needs to be added manually anywhere serious UI manipulation happens:

``` rust
pub struct ResetChildrenInUiSurface;
impl EntityCommand for ResetChildrenInUiSurface {
    fn apply(self, id: Entity, world: &mut World) {
        world.resource_scope(|world, mut ui_surface: Mut<UiSurface>| {
            let Ok(children) = world.query::<&Children>().get(world, id) else {
                return;
            };
            ui_surface.update_children(id, children);
        });
    }
}
```

NOTE: This needs to be done _after_ the UI system builds at least once. Newly created nodes will not be upsert'd into the UiSurface before that (and the upsert is private due to the LayoutConfig being private), so they just throw a warning skipping new children. Interestingly, this works as well, but the warning is annoying.
